#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Armor Class** 8    \n"
"**Hit Points** 22 (3d8 + 9)    \n"
"**Speed** 10 ft., climb 10 ft. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/gray_ooze.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| STR     | DEX     | CON     | INT     | WIS     | CHA     |\n"
"|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|\n"
"| 12 (+1) | 6 (−2)  | 16 (+3) | 1 (−5)  | 6 (−2) |  2 (−4)  |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/gray_ooze.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Skills** Stealth +2    \n"
"**Damage Resistances** acid, cold, fire    \n"
"**Condition Immunities** blinded, charmed, deafened, exhaustion, frightened, "
"prone    \n"
"**Senses** blindsight 60 ft. (blind beyond this radius), passive Perception "
"8    \n"
"**Languages** --    \n"
"**Challenge** 1/2 (100 XP) \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/gray_ooze.md:27
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Amorphous.** The ooze can move through a space as narrow as 1 inch wide "
"without squeezing.    \n"
"**Corrode Metal.** Any nonmagical weapon made of metal that hits the ooze "
"corrodes. After dealing damage, the weapon takes a permanent and cumulative "
"−1 penalty to damage rolls. If its penalty drops to −5, the weapon is "
"destroyed. Nonmagical ammunition made of metal that hits the ooze is "
"destroyed after dealing damage.    \n"
"The ooze can eat through 2-inch-thick, nonmagical metal in 1 round.    \n"
"**False Appearance.** While the ooze remains motionless, it is "
"indistinguishable from an oily pool or wet rock. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/gray_ooze.md:29
msgid ""
"### Actions **Pseudopod.** _Melee Weapon Attack:_ +3 to hit, reach 5 ft., "
"one target. _Hit:_ 4 (1d6 + 1) bludgeoning damage plus 7 (2d6) acid damage, "
"and if the target is wearing nonmagical metal armor, its armor is partly "
"corroded and takes a permanent and cumulative −1 penalty to the AC it "
"offers. The armor is destroyed if the penalty reduces its AC to 10."
msgstr ""
